<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Jungle Grammar Expedition</title>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Luckiest+Guy&family=Nunito:wght@400;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <style>
        :root {
            --jungle-deep: #1b4332;
            --leaf: #40916c;
            --tiger: #fb8500;
            --wood: #603808;
            --sand: #fefae0;
        }

        body {
            font-family: 'Nunito', sans-serif;
            background-color: var(--jungle-deep);
            background-image: url('https://www.transparenttextures.com/patterns/leaves.png');
            margin: 0; padding: 20px;
            display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center;
            min-height: 100vh;
        }

        .expedition-card {
            background: var(--sand);
            max-width: 800px; width: 100%;
            padding: 40px; border-radius: 40px;
            box-shadow: 0 20px 0px rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
            border: 10px solid var(--leaf);
            box-sizing: border-box;
        }

        h1 { 
            font-family: 'Luckiest Guy', cursive; 
            color: var(--jungle-deep); 
            text-align: center; 
            font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 8vw, 4rem); 
            margin: 0 0 20px 0;
            text-shadow: 3px 3px 0px var(--tiger);
        }

        h2 { 
            background: var(--wood); 
            color: var(--sand); 
            padding: 10px 20px; 
            border-radius: 12px; 
            font-size: 1.2rem; 
            margin-top: 30px;
            display: inline-block;
            box-shadow: 4px 4px 0 var(--tiger);
        }

        .task-zone {
            background: rgba(64, 145, 108, 0.15);
            padding: 25px; border-radius: 20px;
            margin: 15px 0; border: 3px dashed var(--leaf);
            line-height: 2.2;
        }

        .word-box {
            background: var(--tiger);
            color: white;
            padding: 10px;
            border-radius: 10px;
            text-align: center;
            font-weight: bold;
            margin-bottom: 15px;
            letter-spacing: 2px;
        }

        input[type="text"] {
            border: none; border-bottom: 3px solid var(--wood);
            background: transparent; outline: none;
            padding: 2px 8px; font-family: 'Nunito', sans-serif;
            font-weight: bold; color: var(--jungle-deep);
            font-size: 1.1rem; transition: 0.3s;
        }

        input[type="text"]:focus { border-bottom-color: var(--tiger); background: rgba(251, 133, 0, 0.1); }

        .btn-check {
            display: block; width: 100%; padding: 25px;
            background: linear-gradient(to bottom, #fb8500, #d66d00);
            color: white; border: none; border-radius: 50px;
            font-size: 1.8rem; font-family: 'Luckiest Guy';
            cursor: pointer; margin-top: 40px;
            box-shadow: 0 8px 0px #8a4a00;
            transition: 0.2s;
        }

        .btn-check:active { transform: translateY(4px); box-shadow: 0 4px 0px #8a4a00; }

        #final-screen { display: none; text-align: center; padding: 40px; }
        .cat-img { width: 100%; max-width: 450px; border-radius: 35px; border: 12px solid white; box-shadow: 0 15px 40px rgba(0,0,0,0.4); }
        .congrats { font-size: 2.5rem; color: white; font-family: 'Luckiest Guy'; margin: 25px 0; text-shadow: 3px 3px 0 var(--tiger); }
        
        .correct-anim { animation: grow 0.5s ease; border-bottom-color: #2d6a4f !important; color: #2d6a4f !important; }
        @keyframes grow { 50% { transform: scale(1.05); } }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="expedition-card" id="game-container">
    <h1>JUNGLE QUEST 🐾</h1>

    <h2>TASK 1: Modals Match</h2>
    <div class="task-zone">
        <div class="word-box">BOX: can’t | could | might | must</div>
        1. It’s definitely not an insect. It <b>can't</b> be an insect.<br>
        2. Perhaps it’s a mole. It <input type="text" style="width: 120px" data-ans="might,could"> be a mole.<br>
        3. It’s definitely dangerous. It <input type="text" style="width: 80px" data-ans="must"> be dangerous.<br>
        4. Maybe it’s harmless. It <input type="text" style="width: 120px" data-ans="might,could"> be harmless.<br>
        5. It’s impossible that they’re bats. They <input type="text" style="width: 80px" data-ans="can't"> be bats.
    </div>

    <h2>TASK 2: The Fox Mystery</h2>
    <div class="task-zone">
        <b>The flying fox</b><br>
        Is it a fox? It’s called a flying fox, but surely a fox (1) <b>can’t</b> fly. Its face looks a bit like a fox’s face, but it definitely (2) <input type="text" style="width: 80px" data-ans="must"> be another type of animal. It’s got wings, but it (3) <input type="text" style="width: 80px" data-ans="can't"> be a bird. In fact, it’s a bat!<br>
        <b>The urban fox</b><br>
        People think that there (4) <input type="text" style="width: 140px" data-ans="might,could"> be over 10,000 foxes living in London. Foxes generally live under the ground, and in the city they surely (5) <input type="text" style="width: 80px" data-ans="must"> live under trees.
    </div>

    <h2>TASK 3: Rewrite the Sentences</h2>
    <div class="task-zone">
        1. It’s possible that it’s a frog. → <i>It could be a frog.</i><br>
        2. I’m certain it isn’t a dangerous animal.<br>
        → <input type="text" style="width: 90%" data-ans="It can't be a dangerous animal"><br>
        3. I’m sure worms are blind.<br>
        → <input type="text" style="width: 90%" data-ans="Worms must be blind"><br>
        4. A cat is definitely not a wild animal.<br>
        → <input type="text" style="width: 90%" data-ans="A cat can't be a wild animal"><br>
        5. Perhaps they’re nocturnal animals.<br>
        → <input type="text" style="width: 90%" data-ans="They might be nocturnal animals,They could be nocturnal animals"><br>
        6. I’m not sure if it’s an insect that stings.<br>
        → <input type="text" style="width: 90%" data-ans="It might be an insect that stings,It could be an insect that stings">
    </div>

    <button class="btn-check" onclick="checkExpedition()">FINISH EXPEDITION 🎒</button>
</div>

<div id="final-screen">
    <div class="congrats">YOU ARE A JUNGLE EXPERT!</div>
    <img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/45201/kitty-cat-baby-psit-45201.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1260&h=750&dpr=1" class="cat-img" alt="Happy Explorer Cat">
    <div class="congrats" id="score-display" style="font-size: 1.5rem;"></div>
    <button class="btn-check" style="width: auto; padding: 15px 50px;" onclick="location.reload()">RESTART QUEST 🔄</button>
</div>

<script>
    function checkExpedition() {
        let score = 0;
        const inputs = document.querySelectorAll('input[data-ans]');
        
        inputs.forEach(input => {
            const userVal = input.value.trim().toLowerCase().replace(/[.’]/g, "'");
            const correctAnswers = input.dataset.ans.toLowerCase().split(',');
            
            if (correctAnswers.includes(userVal)) {
                score++;
                input.classList.add('correct-anim');
            } else {
                input.style.borderBottomColor = "#e63946";
                input.style.color = "#e63946";
            }
        });

        setTimeout(() => {
            document.getElementById('game-container').style.display = 'none';
            document.getElementById('final-screen').style.display = 'block';
            document.getElementById('score-display').innerText = `Completed ${score} out of ${inputs.length} challenges!`;
            window.scrollTo(0,0);
        }, 600);
    }
</script>

</body>
</html>
